I've been waiting for version 20, it's my favourite number !! thanks murphy78.

zavada, that sounds like the process is still running. It really shouldn't give that error.
Try rebooting or taskkilling kmsnano qemu and kmseldi

petrus7, you can extract kmsnano.exe to a directory and run kmseldi.exe /qemu
Just make a shortcut to kmseldi.exe and add the /qemu line.
Then when it warms up the virtual machine after like a minute, press the big "EL" button. It's the same as kms extracted except kms extracted just has a program to hide that.

Lets not give him too hard a time guys, not everyone can tell when an uploader is a total douchebag like T.F.K
